The author, Collin Riddering, shares his experience interning at the White House under President Donald J. Trump. He is serving as an intern in the Office of Presidential Correspondence (OPC), which handles all communication from the American people on behalf of the President. The department receives tens of thousands of emails and thousands of letters daily, and it is their responsibility to carefully examine and respond to each one with the approval of President Trump. OPC also sends specialized letters to individuals who have reached significant milestones in their lives. Additionally, they strive to engage with the American people and provide President Trump with weekly reports on the concerns and opinions of his constituents. Riddering expresses his honor in playing a small role in Making America Great Again and fulfilling President Trump's pledge to work for and listen to the American people.